[Blurb "Akiba Rubinstein's masterpiece — a build-up so harmonious that the final combination feels inevitable. Every black piece converges on the white king at once."]

1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 c5 4. c4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Nf6 6. dxc5 Bxc5 7. a3 a6 8. b4 Bd6
9. Bb2 O-O 10. Qd2 Qe7 11. Bd3 dxc4 12. Bxc4 b5 13. Bd3 Rd8 14. Qe2 Bb7 {Both bishops now rake the long diagonals — Rubinstein's pieces are perfectly placed.}
15. O-O Ne5 16. Nxe5 Bxe5 17. f4 Bc7 18. e4 Rac8 19. e5 Bb6+ 20. Kh1 Ng4 {The knight jumps in; the threats begin to pile up faster than White can meet them.}
21. Be4 Qh4 22. g3 {Forced — but it opens the floodgates.} Rxc3 {The first sacrifice, tearing away a defender.}
23. gxh4 Rd2 {A second rook offered, dragging the queen off the defence.} 24. Qxd2 Bxe4+ 25. Qg2 Rh3 {And White resigned — there is no answer to the mating threat. A flawless combination.}
